==English==
===Adjective===
'''expurgated'''
# Having had [[erroneous]], [[obscene]], or other [[objectionable]] material [[removed]].

----

Example: From [[Monty Python]]

Assistant: Yes, well we do have that one.<br>
Customer: The expurgated version, of course. <br>
Assistant: I'm sorry, I didn't quite catch that. <br>
Customer: The expurgated version. <br>
Assistant: The expurgated version of Olsen's Standard Book of British Birds? <br>
Customer: Yes. It's the one without the gannet. <br>
Assistant: The one without the gannet? They've all got the gannet ... it's a standard bird, the gannet... it's in all the books. <br>
Customer: Well I don't like them, long nasty beaks they've got.<br>